5)  Подключить TON Tonnect 2.0 

TON Connect is a communication protocol between wallets and apps in the TON ecosystem. Wallets do not need to build walled-garden ecosystems themselves, while the apps do not need to take the risk of holding end users’ accounts. TON Connect aims to offer a seamless user experience between the wallets and the apps. Read our recent article, TON Connect – The Future Without Passwords, (https://blog.ton.org/ton-connect-the-future-without-passwords) to better understand the concept and its benefits. Click here (https://github.com/ton-connect) for the TON Connect Github repo.
  PyTon Connect by XaBbl4 (https://github.com/XaBbl4/pytonconnect) – A Python SDK for TON Connect 2.0. This library is the analog of the @tonconnect/sdk library, (https://github.com/ton-connect/sdk/tree/main/packages/sdk) and you can use it to connect your app to TON wallets via the TON Connect protocol. You can find more details and the protocol specification in the docs. (https://github.com/ton-connect/docs)
  TON Connect for Python by ClickoTON Foundation (https://github.com/ClickoTON-Foundation/tonconnect) – Another library for connecting TON Connect to Python apps.


